==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[schmuck]] ''common spelling''

===Etymology===
{{cattag|Yiddish language|Yiddish derivations}} From Yiddish [[שמאָק]] ''shmok'', literally ''[[penis]]'' (''vulgar''), from Old Polish [[smok]] (modern Polish: [[smok]], ''dragon)''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{vulgar}} Of or relating to the [[penis]] or the [[foreskin]].
# {{pejorative}} a [[derogatory]] description of an individual (usually a man.)

